               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18190421-60-person729">
                  HENRY 
                  HART
               <interp inst="t18190421-60-person729" type="surname" value="HART"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190421-60-person729" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190421-60-person729" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 25th of March, about eleven o'clock, I was in <placeName id="t18190421-60-crimeloc345">Cheapside</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18190421-60-crimeloc345" type="placeName" value="Cheapside"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18190421-60-crimeloc345" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18190421-60-off343 t18190421-60-crimeloc345"></join> - there was a little stoppage. As I was making my way through, somebody touched me on the shoulder, and I saw two persons with each a man in custody. Stone had my handkerchief, which I missed.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18190421-60-person730">
                  JOSEPH 
                  STONE
               <interp inst="t18190421-60-person730" type="surname" value="STONE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190421-60-person730" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190421-60-person730" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. On the 25th of March I was with Lewis in Cheapside - a horse was laying in the street, which caused a crowd. I saw the two prisoners and another person following the prosecutor; I let them go by me, and as they were passing I saw Lawrence take the handkerchief from Hart's pocket. I collared him, and took it from him - Lewis took Topley. I am certain they were in company. I saw them talking together.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18190421-60-person731">
                  JOHN 
                  LEWIS
               <interp inst="t18190421-60-person731" type="surname" value="LEWIS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190421-60-person731" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190421-60-person731" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was with Stone, and secured Topley.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>LAWRENCE'S Defence. The other man is innocent.</p>
               <p>LAWRENCE - <rs id="t18190421-60-verdict346" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18190421-60-verdict346" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 19.</p>

